"{\"uid\": \"si.com-golf-2024-paris-olympics-womens-golf-results-lydia-ko-wins-gold-medal\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Lydia Ko is golden, and she made history for New Zealand along the way.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 71, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 8, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lydia_Ko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lydia Ko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lydia_Ko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lydia_Ko\"}, {\"begin\": 45, \"end\": 56, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9995270974717698, \"rank\": 0.00026919183627889857, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ko, 27, entered the round tied for the lead and surged with three front-nine birdies to take the lead outright.\", \"from\": 73, \"to\": 184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But she made a double bogey on the 13th hole to drop from three shots ahead to one over Germany's Esther Henseleit, who finished off a 66 about an hour before Ko to post 8 under and apply pressure.\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 273, \"end\": 280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999001930170567, \"rank\": 9.576444714655756e-05, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 283, \"end\": 299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Esther_Henseleit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Esther Henseleit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Esther_Henseleit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Esther_Henseleit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Ko held on through Le Golf Nationals watery closing holes, avoiding trouble and make four consecutive pars to arrive at the par-5 closing hole with that one-shot lead.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ko laid up on the par 5, knocked a wedge to 6 feet and buried the biride putt to make it a two-shot victory.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Henseleit won silver.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"China's Xiyu Lin finished another shot back to take bronze.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999875631656633, \"rank\": 8.610930666486409e-06, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Regions\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5336570935392017e-24, \"text\": \"Xiyu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Regions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Regions\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the win, Ko adds a gold medal to her silver from the Rio Olympics in 2016 and bronze from Tokyo in 2021.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 807, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7322135775047384e-24, \"text\": \"Rio Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.4357883884018762e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's the only golfer with an Olympic medal of every color.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The win also earned her enough career points to meet the LPGA's Hall of Fame criteria, locking up her spot among the game's all-time greats.\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 1059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the United States, defending gold medalist Nelly Korda finished 1 under par.\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1069, \"end\": 1082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.6292137944931705, \"rank\": 0.5892845802199025, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1108, \"end\": 1119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nelly_Korda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nelly Korda\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nelly_Korda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nelly_Korda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rose Zhang struggled while playing in the final group, shooting a 74 to miss a shot at bronze by three, and Lilia Vu finished 5 over for the event.\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1142, \"end\": 1152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Zhang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rose Zhang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose_Zhang\", \"dbpedia\": \